AnkerGames Source for Hydra Launcher

This repository hosts an automated scraper that generates a valid source file for Hydra Launcher.

How to use this source

Click on the file ankergames.json in the file list above.

Click the "Raw" button in the top right of the file view.

Copy the URL from your browser's address bar. It should look like:
https://raw.githubusercontent.com/YOUR_USERNAME/YOUR_REPO_NAME/main/ankergames.json

Open Hydra Launcher.

Go to Settings -> Download Sources.

Click Import -> Import from URL.

Paste the raw URL and click Add.

How to set this up (For Developers)

If you want to host this yourself:

Create a new Repository on GitHub.

Add the files provided in this guide:

ankergames_scraper.py (The logic)

requirements.txt (The dependencies)

.github/workflows/scraper.yml (The automation)

Push these files to your repository.

Go to the Actions tab in your repository.

You should see "Update AnkerGames Source" listed. You can wait for the daily run, or click "Run workflow" to generate the JSON immediately.

Once the action finishes (green checkmark), a new file named ankergames.json will appear in your code tab.

Click into ankergames.json file and then click raw to get the correct link.

Features

Daily Updates: Runs automatically at 00:00 UTC.

Title Cleaning: Removes version numbers and extra tags for better matching.

Smart Validation: Only adds games that have valid "Direct" download links.
